lead_paragraph: Australian Rod Pampling ended a decade-long drought on the PGA Tour when he won the Shriners Hospitals for Children Open by two strokes from American Brooks Koepka in Las Vegas on Sunday.

headline.print_headline: Golf: Pampling Wins by Two Strokes in Vegas, Ending Long Drought
